  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Key legal elements typically include:\n\n1. Primary components:\n- Concealing the origin of illegally obtained funds\n- Disguising the source of criminal proceeds\n- Transforming \"dirty\" money into seemingly \"clean\" money\n\n2. Common legal definitions include:\n- Intentionally attempting to hide or disguise the source of criminal proceeds\n- Engaging in financial transactions designed to conceal criminal activity\n- Transferring funds to obscure their illegal origins\n\n3. Typical legal requirements for prosecution:\n- Proving intent to conceal criminal proceeds\n- Demonstrating knowledge of the funds' illegal source\n- Showing deliberate financial manipulation\n\n4. International standards often include:\n- Currency transactions over specific reporting thresholds\n- Suspicious transaction reporting requirements\n- Cross-border money movement regulations\n\n5. Common methods considered illegal:\n- Structuring bank deposits\n- Shell company transactions\n- Complex international transfers\n- Cash-intensive business manipulation\n\nNote: Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, so consulting local legal statutes is recommended for precise details.",
